{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-markdown-js","path":"/users/apps/docs/ocp_dev_environments/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Operate First"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0ceb96b1-6ffb-5cee-8bdb-7ddf65679c63","html":"<h2 id=\"getting-access-to-ocp-in-for-development\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#getting-access-to-ocp-in-for-development\" aria-label=\"getting access to ocp in for development permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting access to OCP in for Development</h2>\n<p>Below is a list of methods you can get your own OCP 4.0+ environment for development/testing purposes:</p>\n<h2 id=\"crc\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#crc\" aria-label=\"crc permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>CRC</h2>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>\n<p>Setup CRC <a href=\"https://developers.redhat.com/products/codeready-containers/overview\">https://developers.redhat.com/products/codeready-containers/overview</a></p>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>Do not forget to install the corresponding version of <code class=\"language-text\">oc</code> tool or some commands might fail.</li>\n<li>With the latest CRC, you can setup memory, CPU and disk side at the command line when starting CRC for the first time. E.g.:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">crc start -c 4 -d 64 -m 32768 -p  /home/big/crc-pull-secret.txt</code></pre></div>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>You can also add <a href=\"./crc-disk-size.md\">more disk space</a> to your existing CRC image.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"quicklab\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#quicklab\" aria-label=\"quicklab permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Quicklab</h2>\n<p>Note: Only applicable to Red Hat Employees</p>\n<p>Follow the instructions <a href=\"./setup_quicklab.md\">here</a> to set up your Quicklab environment.</p>","fields":{"srcLink":"https://github.com/operate-first/apps/blob/master/docs/ocp_dev_environments/README.md"},"frontmatter":{"title":"","description":null,"extraClasses":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"0ceb96b1-6ffb-5cee-8bdb-7ddf65679c63"}},"staticQueryHashes":["117426894","3000541721","3606484676","533861647"]}